OL,3,CAnger as 'no progress is made' to help
OL,4,Cflood-hit businesses
OL,6,FDaniel Adams, from Stationery House,
OL,7,Fsaid when he arrived at 8am the road
OL,8,Fwas clear and it was persistently
OL,9,Fraining. However, very quickly the
OL,10,Fdrain was blocked and the road started
OL,11,Fto flood.
OL,13,F"By 10am (the road) was completely
OL,14,Funderwater, up to our front door and
OL,15,Fby 11am it was in the shop."
OL,17,FHe said passing traffic made things
OL,18,Fworse, creating a tidal wave.
