OL,3,CAnger as 'no progress is made' to help
OL,4,Cflood-hit businesses
OL,6,F"Even the sandbags we put down weren't
OL,7,Fstopping an onslaught of water. We
OL,8,Flost over #150 worth of stock because
OL,9,Fthe water was getting everywhere
OL,10,Fquicker than we could stop it.
OL,12,F"It is really sad because you're
OL,13,Ftrying to make a go of it as an
OL,14,Findependent retailer."
OL,16,FDaniel said for years Wessex Water and
OL,17,FNorth Somerset Council have argued
OL,18,Fover who is responsible for the drain
OL,19,Fproblems that occur when there's heavy
OL,20,Frain, but no progress is made.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
