OL,3,CAnger as 'no progress is made' to help
OL,4,Cflood-hit businesses
OL,6,F"Every time it rains we're back to
OL,7,Fsquare one, dealing with these issues."
OL,9,FNext door, The Signature Salon, had
OL,10,Fvery similar problems.
OL,12,FSharron Trotter, from the salon, said:
OL,13,F"It was ankle deep. You couldn't see
OL,14,Fthe edge of the pavement from the
OL,15,Froad. If the cars came too close and
OL,16,Fwent too fast, the water actually came
OL,17,Funder the door and the doormat was
OL,18,Ffloating with so much water.
OL,20,F"If we can't get the customers in, we
OL,21,Fcan't keep the business going."
